</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VINCENT BOLAND
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AER LINGUS has reduced the value of its stake in GPA Group, the aircraft
leasing group, by IPounds 21.9m (Pounds 20.6m) in its accounts for the year
to March 31.
Its 8.76 per cent stake is valued at about IPounds 113m, based on exchange
rates ruling at March 31.
This implies a price of Dollars 18.50 for each GPA share at March 31,
compared to the range of Dollars 20-Dollars 25 a share (before a two-for-one
