<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUL 92 / Local elections in Albania
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TIRANA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Albanians went to the polls yesterday in the first local elections since the
anti-communist Democrats swept to power in national elections in March,
Reuter reports from Tirana. The mood in the Tirana was quiet despite a
heated pre-election campaign in which the key forces were the Democratic
party, which is the biggest anti-communist force, and the Socialist party,
the renamed communists.
