<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JUL 92 / Finance &amp; The Family: Smaller companies gloom deepens
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Small companies had another terrible week. Share prices in smaller companies
have now been falling consistently for two months. The Hoare Govett Smaller
Companies index (capital gains version) fell 3.69 per cent to 1092.23 over
the seven days to Thursday, July 23, while the County NatWest index fell by
3.49 per cent to 869.47.
</TEXT>
