The issue was priced at DKr105 a share, but the B shares traded at about
DKr95 during the period of the issue.
Before the issue, now fully subscribed, Hafnia's equity capital was a
negative DKr450m.
It is expected that substantial cuts in staff and the sale of some
subsidiaries will be announced in the autumn.
