<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Pendragon expands dealerships
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pendragon, a distributor of luxury and executive cars, has increased its
Jaguar franchises in the UK to five and its Land Rover franchises to four
through the acquisition for Pounds 2.8m cash of Stratstone, the central
London dealer.
Stratstone has showrooms in Mayfair and the City; its annual turnover is
some Pounds 21m.
Pendragon has also agreed with Mercedes-Benz UK to set up a new greenfield
dealership in Wakefield, starting operations in October. It will then trade
from four Mercedes-Benz passenger car dealerships.
