FT  25 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Former MAM chief takes post at Jupiter
Tyndall
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR LEONARD LICHT, former vice-chairman of Mercury Asset Management, has
moved to the Jupiter Tyndall Group, another fund manager, where he will be
group managing director and deputy chairman.
Mr Licht's departure follows those of Mr James Dawnay, formerly in charge of
MAM's unit trust business, to Baillie Gifford, and Mr Richard Bernays, a
Mercury vice-chairman, to Hill Samuel.
Mr Licht enjoys a strong reputation as a fund manager, and will work on the
management of pension funds and other institutional clients.
Mr John Duffield, chairman of Jupiter Tyndall, said: ' We have no doubt that
as a fund manager Leonard is unsurpassed in his generation and he will
enormously strengthen our team.'
Mr Peter Stormonth Darling, chairman of MAM, announced that Mr Stephen
Zimmerman, Mercury's deputy chairman, will take day-to-day responsibility
for the group's specialist equity division with immediate effect following
Mr Licht's departure.
