Sir, The building societies feel aggrieved and hold National Savings
responsible for savers withdrawing funds from them. Strange that some
societies seem to have ignored the fact that for some time they have
persuaded savers to deposit funds with them, initially at competitive rates,
only for savers to find shortly after that interest rates have been
unilaterally reduced without them being informed.
Could we be getting our own back?
