General Dynamics recently carried out a Dutch auction tender offer to buy
back 13.2m of its shares at a price of Dollars 72.25 a share. It is
committed to return to investors much of the excess cash the business is
throwing off.
Members and trusts of Chicago's Crown and Goodman families reduced their
stake is from 22 per cent to about 14.4 per cent under the Dutch auction.
