<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JUL 92 / International Company News: Cash flow troubles Carolco
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CAROLCO, the embattled Hollywood studio whose hit films, including
Terminator 2, have not been enough to keep it from the brink of bankruptcy,
said it had severe liquidity problems because of its continuing inability to
draw under its bank credit facilities, writes Karen Zagor in New York.
The company's wholly-owned television subsidiary also confirmed it was
discussing the sale of some US television rights to its film library with
Spelling Entertainment for about Dollars 69m.
The terms of the deal with Spelling would be similar to an earlier
agreement, which expired this summer without completion. Spelling would buy
some US distribution rights to more than 150 films, including the
recently-released Basic Instinct and Terminator 2.
</TEXT>
